The correction of thermal ink
The size of the thermal ink sensing area is thought as M pixels, the value of each pixel point Pi is g(i)=(Ri,Gi,Bi),i=1,2,â¯,M. So, the average value of the color intensity in the entire sensing area R=âi=1Mg(i)/M\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
